This article is about the proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump to commemorate General Casimir Pulaski. General Pulaski, a Polish immigrant, played a significant role in the American Revolutionary War and is known as the "Father of the American Cavalry." He fought for freedom in both Poland and the United States and demonstrated bravery and leadership. General Pulaski died in battle, and his devotion to the American cause earned him honorary citizenship. The proclamation recognizes General Pulaski's defense of Polish-American values and the close bond between the United States and Poland. It also acknowledges the contributions of Americans of Polish descent and encourages all Americans to commemorate those who have contributed to the nation.